savage /ˈsævɪdʒ/

(savaging,savaged,savages) 

1. ADJ Someone or something that is savage is extremely cruel, violent, and uncontrolled. 野蛮的; 残暴的 

例： This was a savage attack on a defenceless young girl. 这是对一个无力自卫的小姑娘的野蛮袭击。 

例： ...the savage wave of violence that swept the country in November 

1987. …1987年11月席卷了该国的野蛮暴力浪潮。 

2. savagely ADV 野蛮地; 残暴地 

例： He was savagely beaten. 他被毒打了。 

3. N-COUNT If you refer to people as savages , you dislike them because you think that they do not have an advanced society and are violent. 野蛮人; 残暴的人 [表不满] 

例： ...their conviction that the area was a frozen desert peopled with uncouth savages. …他们深信该地区是一片冰冷的沙漠，住着一些没有教养的野蛮人。 

4. V-T If someone is savaged by a dog or other animal, the animal attacks them violently. (动物) 凶猛地攻击 [usu passive] 

例： The animal then turned on him and he was savaged to death. 那只兽接而扑向他，把他攻击至死。

